&lt;p&gt;You can as well check this other extension to assign classes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://pythonhosted.org/Markdown/extensions/attr_list.html"&gt;attribule lists extension&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Footnotes&lt;sup id="fnref:1"&gt;&lt;a class="footnote-ref" href="#fn:1" rel="footnote"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; have a label&lt;sup id="fnref:@#$%"&gt;&lt;a class="footnote-ref" href="#fn:@#$%" rel="footnote"&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; and the footnote&amp;rsquo;s content.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="framed"&gt;Whatch this as well, it looks like this: &lt;code&gt;text {: .framed}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="meta"&gt;or something a bot more like this&lt;/p&gt;
